# Plan: Show Changelog Summary During CLI Upgrade (#421)

## Summary

Add inline changelog summaries to `sentry cli upgrade` output. When upgrading from version A to B, display a flat summary of new features, bug fixes, and performance improvements across the entire version delta. Uses `marked.lexer()` for AST-based section extraction and `renderMarkdown()` for output. Dynamically clamps entry count to ~1.3x terminal height. Zero added latency ŌĆö fetch runs in parallel with binary download.

## Feasibility: Fully feasible

- GitHub Releases API returns `body` with structured release notes ŌĆö currently discarded by `fetchRecentReleases()`
- `marked` (v15) is already a dependency ŌĆö provides full AST lexer for section extraction
- `renderMarkdown()` handles all ANSI styling, plain mode, tables, lists
- Nightly versions encode commit timestamps (`X.Y.Z-dev.<unix-seconds>`) ŌĆö enables timestamp-based commit listing via GitHub Commits API with zero CI changes
- Parallel fetch adds zero latency to the upgrade flow

