## Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Choice | Rationale |
|----------|--------|-----------|
| Section extraction | `marked.lexer()` AST walk | Already a dependency; structured parsing instead of fragile regex |
| Output rendering | `renderMarkdown()` on reconstructed markdown | Consistent styling (headings, lists, links, code spans) with rest of CLI |
| Terminal height clamping | `maxItems = termHeight * 1.3 - 6` | Shows more than one screen but not overwhelming; 30 default for non-TTY |
| Flat delta | Merge same-category sections across releases | Users care about total delta, not which release introduced each change |
| Token preservation | Store `Token[]` in `ChangeSection` | Avoids lossy string conversion; enables both re-serialization and counting |
| Nightly support | Timestamp-based GitHub Commits API | No CI changes needed; conventional commits provide structure |
| Categories kept | features, fixes, performance only | Internal changes, docs, refactoring filtered as not user-relevant |

## Edge Cases

| Scenario | Behavior |
|----------|----------|
| Offline mode | Skip changelog entirely |
| GitHub rate limited / network error | Return null, upgrade proceeds silently |
| >12 stable releases spanned | Show changes from most recent 12 (rare; ~3 months of releases) |
| Nightly with large commit range | GitHub Commits API returns up to 250 per page; sufficient |
| Downgrade | Show changelog with "being reverted" note |
| All entries filtered out (only internal changes) | No "What's new" section shown |
| Non-TTY / piped output | Use 30-item default; `renderMarkdown()` handles plain mode |
| `--json` mode | `changelog` field included with structured sections |
| Very small terminal (e.g., 10 rows) | `maxItems` floors at 5 to always show something |

